  <p><strong>Quick Answer:</strong> Zinfandel excels with grilled meats, barbecue, and tomato-based dishes. Its bold fruit flavors and moderate tannins complement smoky, spicy foods while cutting through rich sauces. Match lighter Zinfandels with chicken and pork, reserve intense old-vine bottles for beef and lamb.</p>
